    <note>Luo(1) Bowen [26774] Listed in Fujian TZ and CBD as a 1202 jinshi, which is clearly impossible. The funerary inscriptions have him entering public service on the basis of the yin of his grandfather. The 1202 jinshi may be a grandson, but not entered. He was married to the granddauther of Chen(1) Guan's [7128] elder brother. I arbitrarily select Chen(1) Jue(2) [13703], but it could be Yuan(3) [13702]. Zhu Xi, WJ, 97.31a-34b; Wang Yingchen, WJ, 22.273-4. CBD, 5, 4285.</note>
